gomodel:SYNGO_3052  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2:\n- \" Western blotting of subcellular fractions revealed that both drosha and DGCR8 were present in synaptic fractions and, within synaptosomes, were predominantly associated with PSDs (Fig. 2c).\"\n- \"PSD-95 immunoprecipitates contained drosha and DGCR8 (Fig. 2b). \". Experimental description: - \"Two-month-old male C57Bl/6 mice were employed in this study\"" ;
